cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep network architecture for scene classification that models the semantic context of scenes by capturing object-level information. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) units to incorporate object-object relationship and object-scene relationship in an end-to-end trainable manner. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for modeling context, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of LSTM units suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
